<!-- ================= FAQ ================= -->
<section style="background:#15302f;padding:100px 32px;">
  <div style="max-width:1180px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div style="margin-bottom:44px;text-align:center;" data-reveal>
      <p class="of-eyebrow">// FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="of-display of-text-white" style="font-size:clamp(28px,3.6vw,44px);line-height:1.0;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:-0.5px;">Common Questions</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="of-faq-grid">
      <div class="of-faq-img" data-reveal>
        <img src="{{ diver_img }}" alt="Ocean Forged in the field" loading="lazy">
      </div>
      <div class="of-faq-list" data-of-faq>
        <div class="of-faq-item">
          <button type="button" class="of-faq-q" data-faq-toggle>
            <h3>What's the best waterproof case for a lifeguard radio?</h3>
            <span class="of-faq-plus">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="of-faq-a"><p>Look for three things: a true submersible rating (not just splash resistant), a hands-free carry system, and a seal built for constant daily use, not occasional storms. The RDB-01 covers all three with RF-welded TPU construction and a cross-body harness built specifically for lifeguard shifts.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="of-faq-item">
          <button type="button" class="of-faq-q" data-faq-toggle>
            <h3>Is the RDB-01 actually waterproof, or just water resistant?</h3>
            <span class="of-faq-plus">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="of-faq-a"><p>It's fully waterproof, rated for submersion, not just rain or splashes. The RF-welded seams and Tru Zip closure are built to handle full immersion, which matters if you're going into the water with your radio still on you.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="of-faq-item">
          <button type="button" class="of-faq-q" data-faq-toggle>
            <h3>Can you still talk and hear through the bag?</h3>
            <span class="of-faq-plus">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="of-faq-a"><p>Yes. The TPU material is designed so you can operate the radio and hear clearly through the case without opening it.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="of-faq-item">
          <button type="button" class="of-faq-q" data-faq-toggle>
            <h3>How do you wear the RDB-01 during a shift?</h3>
            <span class="of-faq-plus">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="of-faq-a"><p>It comes with a cross-body harness, so it sits secure against your body while you run, swim, or respond to a rescue, no fumbling with a strap.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="of-faq-item">
          <button type="button" class="of-faq-q" data-faq-toggle>
            <h3>What's the RDB-01 made of?</h3>
            <span class="of-faq-plus">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="of-faq-a"><p>RF-welded TPU with a Tru Zip waterproof zipper, built for daily exposure to saltwater, sand, and sun, not just occasional use.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="of-faq-item">
          <button type="button" class="of-faq-q" data-faq-toggle>
            <h3>What does RF-welded mean?</h3>
            <span class="of-faq-plus">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="of-faq-a"><p>RF welding (radio frequency welding) fuses seams together with heat and pressure instead of stitching or glue, so there are no needle holes for water to work through. It's the same seam technique used in dry bags and medical-grade waterproof gear, and it's why the RDB-01 doesn't leak at the seams.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="of-faq-item">
          <button type="button" class="of-faq-q" data-faq-toggle>
            <h3>What is TPU?</h3>
            <span class="of-faq-plus">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="of-faq-a"><p>TPU stands for thermoplastic polyurethane, a flexible, durable material that holds up to saltwater, abrasion, and UV exposure better than standard vinyl or PVC. It's why the RDB-01 stays waterproof and doesn't crack or degrade after repeated ocean, sun, and sand exposure.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

