        "text": "It's fully waterproof, rated for submersion, not just rain or splashes. The RF-welded seams and Tru Zip closure are built to handle full immersion, which matters if you're going into the water with your radio still on you."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you still talk and hear through the bag?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. The TPU material is designed so you can operate the radio and hear clearly through the case without opening it."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do you wear the RDB-01 during a shift?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "It comes with a cross-body harness, so it sits secure against your body while you run, swim, or respond to a rescue, no fumbling with a strap."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What's the RDB-01 made of?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "RF-welded TPU with a Tru Zip waterproof zipper, built for daily exposure to saltwater, sand, and sun, not just occasional use."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does RF-welded mean?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "RF welding (radio frequency welding) fuses seams together with heat and pressure instead of stitching or glue, so there are no needle holes for water to work through. It's the same seam technique used in dry bags and medical-grade waterproof gear, and it's why the RDB-01 doesn't leak at the seams."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is TPU?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "TPU stands for thermoplastic polyurethane, a flexible, durable material that holds up to saltwater, abrasion, and UV exposure better than standard vinyl or PVC. It's why the RDB-01 stays waterproof and doesn't crack or degrade after repeated ocean, sun, and sand exposure."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

